3 SECTION 5. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1280.4 of Title 59, unless there
5 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 A. The State Commissioner of Health shall promulgate rules to:
7 1. Adopt a set of standards for the approval of certified
8 community health workers' initial coursework or curriculum;
9 2. Establish examination administration requirements for the
10 Department or one or more designees;
11 3. Define minimum qualifications for applicants to be
12 certified; and
13 4. Establish the criteria for granting, renewing, denying,
14 suspending, and revoking a certificate to uphold health standards
15 and safety.
16 B. The Commissioner may also promulgate rules to establish
17 partnerships with faith-based organizations to enhance community
18 health outreach and service delivery, including, but not limited to:
19 1. Recognizing faith-based organizations as eligible entities
20 for community health care worker training and certification programs
21 when they meet established state standards;
22 2. Facilitating collaboration between community health care
23 workers and faith-based organizations to improve health access,
24 prevention, and health literacy efforts in underserved communities;
Req. No. 13185 Page 4

1 3. Supporting faith-based health initiatives through technical
2 assistance and programmatic support for community health care
3 workers working within congregations and religious institutions;
4 4. Encouraging the integration of community health care workers
5 into existing faith-based outreach programs to enhance culturally
6 competent care and strengthen trust in community health efforts.
7 C. The Commissioner shall prescribe fees for the certified
8 community health worker examination, initial certification, and
9 certification renewal.
10 SECTION 6. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
